Key Match Events: Stephen Curry returned from an ankle injury and scored a season-high 24 points, including 15 points in the third quarter.
Warriors' defense held Wizards' Jordan Poole to 2-10 shooting from three-point range and limited Bilal Coulibaly to a season-low nine points.
Warriors won the rebounding battle 56-47 and held the Wizards to 23 percent shooting from distance.
